and peeled garlic</p><p>Heat the oil in a large frypan on a medium-high heat</p><p>Add diced ingredients and cook stirring often for 10 minutes</p><p>Bring a pot of water to boil and add the pasta, cook for 12-15 minutes</p><p>Mix in the Tomato Paste and stir occasionally while allowing the soffrito to burn slightly</p><p>Add the beef mince to the pan and leave to crisp before before breaking up, 3-5 minutes, then mix into the soffrito and allow the mince to cook through</p><p>Pour the passata into the pan and mix together</p><p>** Add optional ingredients and combine **</p><p>Allow mixture to simmer to a consistency of your preference</p>]]></content:encoded></item></channel></rss>